        <updateDate>2019-08-26T22:21:24Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Social Security Disability Fairness Act of 2017 </b></p> <p>This bill allows an individual diagnosed with a terminal illness to receive disability payments under the Old Age, Survivors, and Disability Insurance program during the waiting period for such payments (which typically lasts five months). It also establishes a phased-in payment schedule for such payments. </p> <p>These provisions shall expire January 1, 2023. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
